The paper proposes a model for lifelong learning that involves a network of experts, which suggests that it could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments conducted in the paper involve image classification and video prediction, which are both computer vision tasks, indicating that it could also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of autoencoders, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of memory efficiency, which is a topic that falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as text classification, which suggests that it could also belong to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
